    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="164" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 10,
                                    1896</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sill</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister, Seoul:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Your dispatches Nos. 175, 176, and 177 received. Your course in continued
                            intermeddling with Korean political affairs in violation of repeated
                            instructions noted with astonishment and emphatic disapproval. Cable
                            briefly any explanation you have to make; also answer whether you intend
                            to comply with instructions given.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
